---
---
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>Heartwood Stand</title>

    <style>
      :root {
        --bg: #f5f1ea;
        --surface: #fbf8f3;
        --text: #1f1c17;
        --muted: #5e5a53;
        --accent: #6f7c68;
        --max-width: 760px;
      }

      * {
        box-sizing: border-box;
      }

      html,
      body {
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
      }

      body {
        font-family: Georgia, "Times New Roman", serif;
        background: var(--bg);
        color: var(--text);
        line-height: 1.7;
      }

      img {
        display: block;
        max-width: 100%;
      }

.hero {
  position: relative;
  min-height: 72vh;
  display: flex;
  align-items: flex-end;
  justify-content: flex-start;
  overflow: hidden;
}

      .hero img {
        position: absolute;
        inset: 0;
        width: 100%;
        height: 100%;
        object-fit: cover;
      }

      .hero::before {
        content: "";
        position: absolute;
        inset: 0;
        background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.34);
        z-index: 1;
      }

 .hero-content {
  position: relative;
  z-index: 2;
  text-align: left;
  color: white;
  max-width: 700px;
  padding: 3rem 2rem 4rem 3rem;
}

      .hero-content h1 {
        margin: 0 0 1rem;
	margin-left: 0;
        font-size: clamp(2.8rem, 7vw, 5.5rem);
        line-height: 1.02;
        font-weight: 600;
        letter-spacing: 0.02em;
        text-shadow: 0 3px 18px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.35);
      }

      .hero-content p {
        margin: 0;
        font-size: clamp(1.1rem, 2.4vw, 1.5rem);
        line-height: 1.5;
        text-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.35);
      }

      .content-section {
        max-width: var(--max-width);
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 4rem 1.5rem;
      }

      .content-section h2 {
        font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4vw, 2.4rem);
        line-height: 1.15;
        margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
      }

      .content-section p {
        margin: 0 0 1.35rem;
        font-size: 1.08rem;
        color: var(--text);
      }

      .content-section p:last-child {
        margin-bottom: 0;
      }

      .intro {
        background: var(--surface);
      }

      .process {
        background: var(--bg);
      }

      footer {
        padding: 2.5rem 1.5rem 3rem;
        text-align: center;
        color: var(--muted);
        font-size: 0.98rem;
      }

      @media (max-width: 640px) {
        .hero {
          min-height: 62vh;
        }

        .content-section {
          padding: 3rem 1.25rem;
        }
      }
.site-header {
  position: absolute;
  top: 0;
  left: 0;
  width: 100%;
  z-index: 3;
  padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
}

.site-nav {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: space-between;
  gap: 1rem;
}

.site-brand a {
  color: white;
  text-decoration: none;
  font-size: 1rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  font-weight: 600;
  text-shadow: 0 2px 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.35);
}

.site-menu {
  display: flex;
  gap: 1.25rem;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
}

.site-menu a {
  color: white;
  text-decoration: none;
  font-size: 0.95rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  text-shadow: 0 2px 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.35);
  padding-bottom: 0.15rem;
  border-bottom: 1px solid transparent;
  transition: border-color 0.2s ease, opacity 0.2s ease;
}

.site-menu a:hover {
  border-bottom-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
  opacity: 0.95;
}
    </style>
  </head>

  <body>
<header class="site-header">
  <nav class="site-nav">
    <div class="site-brand">
      <a href="/">Heartwood Stand</a>
    </div>

    <div class="site-menu">
      <a href="/">Home</a>
      <a href="#intro">Intro</a>
      <a href="#gallery">Gallery</a>
      <a href="#process">Process</a>
      <a href="#footer">Contact</a>
    </div>
  </nav>
</header>
    <!-- HERO -->
    <section class="hero">
      <img src="/images/mist.jpeg" alt="Mist over trees" />

      <div class="hero-content">
        <h1>Heartwood Stand</h1>
        <p>
          <em>Work that starts in the forest.<br />
          Some of it starts earlier.</em>
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- INTRO -->
    <section class="intro" id="intro">
      <div class="content-section">
        <p>
          Some of the work begins on a bench.
          Some of it begins a little earlier.
        </p>

        <p>
          Heartwood Stand follows wood from where it falls to whatever it becomes next — logs, boards, projects, mistakes, finished pieces, and the occasional good idea.
        </p>

        <p>
          The goal isn’t perfection.
          Just useful things, honest material, and the satisfaction of making something solid.
        </p>

        <p>
          The work might start in the forest.
          But it’s a jungle out there.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- PROCESS -->
    <section class="process" id="process">
      <div class="content-section">
        <h2>From forest to form</h2>

        <p>
          Fallen timber. Milling. Drying. Shaping.
          Sometimes building. Sometimes rebuilding.
          Sometimes just standing there looking at a log,
          wondering what it wants to become.
        </p>

        <p>
          This site is a place to keep track of the work,
          the land, the tools, and whatever comes out of them.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FOOTER -->
    <footer>
      <p>
        Heartwood Stand<br />
        Work that starts in the forest.
      </p>
    </footer>
  </body>
</html>